fullName.value: Tumor necrosis factor type 1 receptor-associated protein

texts.value: Chaperone that expresses an ATPase activity. Involved in maintaining mitochondrial function and polarization, downstream of PINK1 and mitochondrial complex I. Is a negative regulator of mitochondrial respiration able to modulate the balance between oxidative phosphorylation and aerobic glycolysis. The impact of TRAP1 on mitochondrial respiration is probably mediated by modulation of mitochondrial SRC and inhibition of SDHA
Binds to the intracellular domain of tumor necrosis factor type 1 receptor. Binds to RB1. Interacts with SRC. Interacts with SDHA

Found in skeletal muscle, liver, heart, brain, kidney, pancreas, lung, placenta and bladder. Expression is highly reduced in bladder cancer and renal cell carcinoma specimens compared to healthy tissues, but it is increased in other type of tumors
Belongs to the heat shock protein 90 family
